The paper deals with a scheduling problem, which is a classic topic in computer science and falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The problem involves processing times and precedence constraints, which are related to combinatorial optimization (cs.DM) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also proposes a dynamic programming algorithm, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and information theory (cs.IT).
